SIMPLE: undercharge
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Undercharge
<hw>Un`der*charge"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To charge below or under; to charge less than is usual or suitable
for; <as>as, to <ex>undercharge</ex> goods or services</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To put too small a charge into; <as>as, to
<ex>undercharge</ex> a gun</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Undercharged mine</b></col> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>, <cd>a mine
whose crater is not as wide at top as it is deep.</cd> <rj><au>W. P.
Craighill.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undercharge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Undercharge
<hw>Un"der*charge`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A charge that
is less than is usual or suitable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underclay</ent>⟦br⟧
